        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:08PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 208 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 10 miles southwest of Winnfield to 7
miles southwest of Campti, or extending from 10 miles southwest of
Winnfield to 7 miles northwest of Natchitoches, moving northeast at
5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Natchitoches, Campti, Clarence, Calvin, Powhatan, Clear Lake,
Grand Ecore, St. Maurice and Lake End.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
